vocabulary.definition: something silly or absurd; foolish talk or ideas
vocabulary.example: Don't listen to him, it's just nonsense.

vocabulary.definition: the events that will necessarily happen to a particular person or thing in the future
vocabulary.example: She believed it was her destiny to become a famous singer.

vocabulary.definition: to remain in one place in the air; to linger uncertainly
vocabulary.example: The helicopter hovered overhead, watching the scene below.

vocabulary.definition: fate, fortune, or destiny; the way one's life is set to unfold
vocabulary.example: She accepted her lot in life and made the best of it.

vocabulary.definition: something given as a gift or sacrifice, especially to a deity
vocabulary.example: The villagers made an offering to the gods for a bountiful harvest.

vocabulary.definition: collecting or gathering of a crop when it's ripe
vocabulary.example: During autumn, farmers are busy harvesting their crops.
